&lt;p&gt;Qpoint EQA scheme are looking for an enthusiastic, committed individual to join the team. We are looking for a person with a great eye for detail, good admin skill set and has had experience of customer liaison&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BSPS provides Pathology services, including POCT, to Ashford &amp; St Peters Hospital, The Royal Surrey County Hospital, Royal Berkshire Foundation Trust, Royal Berkshire Foundation Trust and Frimley Health NHS Foundation Trust. The Qpoint team are located at Aldershot Centre for Health, we are a small team of individuals passionate about quality of the services provided to our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Qpoint provides External Quality Assessment Schemes for POCT devices throughout the UK with the potential to expand internationally. Approximately 6000 samples are distributed each month from the Qpoint laboratory.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique role within the Trust and Berkshire and Surrey Pathology Services. The post holder may be asked to work at any of the numerous sites in primary and secondary care where services are delivered by BSPS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity to be involved in making a difference in quality led health care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To find out more about this role please contact David Baulch or Poppy Watts, Qpoint Deputy Manager and Coordinator&lt;/p&gt;
